<title>USA: First Data sets 20.4 mln share buyback.</title>
<headline>First Data sets 20.4 mln share buyback.</headline>
<dateline>HACKENSACK, N.J. 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>First Data Corp said its board has authorized the repurchase of up to 20.4 million shares of common stock.</p>
<p>It said the buyback program is in anticipation of meeting the conversion requirements of $443.1 million of senior convertible debt which were guaranteed by First Data following its 1995 merger with First Financial Management Corp.</p>
<p>Repurchase activity will be financed primarily with proceeds from the sale of its First Health Strategies and First Health Services units and from new borrowings, according to First Data.</p>
